<sect1 id="particle_template_page_1particle_template_intro">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para>The <ref refid="classparticle__template" kindref="compound">particle_template</ref> class represents physics particles (objects) within events. It provides the base interface for particle properties and operations.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="particle_template_page_1particle_template_properties">
<title>Standard Properties</title>
<para>Particles typically have:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Kinematic properties (pT, eta, phi, E, m)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Identification (type, charge)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Quality flags</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Truth information</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
